# Omniposting Development Guidelines

## Current Deployment Status
- Frontend: https://omniposting.com (DigitalOcean)
- Backend API: https://api.omniposting.com (DigitalOcean)
- Database: Neon PostgreSQL
- Infrastructure: DigitalOcean Droplet (137.184.15.8)

## Development Streams

### UI/UX Development Stream
Focus: Frontend visual design and user experience
Branch Naming: devin/ui-*

Key Responsibilities:
- Page layouts and components
- Responsive design implementation
- Visual theme consistency
- User interaction flows
- Form designs and validation UI
- Loading states and animations
- Error handling UI

Development Guidelines:
1. Visual Theme:
   - Dark mode interface with purple gradients
   - Clean, minimalist form design
   - Modern typography
   - Social login options styling
   - Consistent "Back to website" navigation

2. Key Pages:
   - Login/Signup
   - Dashboard
   - Calendar Interface
   - Analytics Dashboard
   - Team Management
   - Profile Settings

3. Component Guidelines:
   - Reusable components in packages/frontend/src/components/*
   - Styled using Tailwind CSS
   - Responsive design for all viewports
   - Consistent loading states
   - Error boundary implementation

4. Testing:
   - Visual regression testing
   - Responsive design testing
   - Cross-browser compatibility
   - Accessibility compliance

5. Deployment:
   - Changes automatically deploy to https://omniposting.com
   - Preview deployments available for PRs
   - Visual QA on live development site

### Backend Development Stream
Focus: API development, infrastructure, and core functionality
Branch Naming: devin/backend-*

Key Responsibilities:
- API endpoint implementation
- Database schema management
- Authentication flows
- Social media integrations
- Analytics processing
- Performance optimization
- Security implementation

Development Guidelines:
1. API Development:
   - RESTful endpoints in packages/backend/src/routes/*
   - OpenAPI/Swagger documentation
   - Strong type definitions
   - Comprehensive error handling
   - Rate limiting implementation

2. Core Features:
   - Social media post scheduling
   - Analytics data collection
   - Team collaboration features
   - Automated reporting system
   - Platform integration management

3. Database:
   - Prisma schema management
   - Migration handling
   - Query optimization
   - Data validation

4. Security:
   - JWT authentication
   - Role-based access control
   - API key management
   - Input validation
   - Security headers

5. Testing:
   - Unit tests for business logic
   - Integration tests for API
   - Performance benchmarking
   - Security testing

## File Ownership

1. UI/UX Team Files:
   ```
   packages/frontend/src/app/*        # Page components
   packages/frontend/src/components/* # Reusable components
   packages/frontend/src/styles/*     # Theme and styling
   packages/frontend/public/*         # Static assets
   ```

2. Backend Team Files:
   ```
   packages/backend/*                # Express.js backend
   packages/backend/prisma/*         # Database schema
   packages/backend/src/routes/*     # API endpoints
   packages/backend/src/services/*   # Business logic
   deployment/*                      # Infrastructure
   ```

## Development Setup

1. Environment Setup:
   ```bash
   # Clone repository
   gh repo clone Ransomxo/social-media-app
   cd social-media-app

   # Install dependencies
   pnpm install

   # Set up environment variables (request access from team lead)
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

2. Access Management:
   - GitHub access: Request from repository admin
   - Environment variables: Use secure credential management
   - Infrastructure access: Coordinate with DevOps team
   - Database access: Request from database admin

3. Local Development:
   ```bash
   # Start frontend
   cd packages/frontend
   pnpm dev

   # Start backend
   cd packages/backend
   pnpm dev
   ```

## Deployment Process

1. Frontend (omniposting.com):
   - Automatic deployment on main branch
   - SSL/HTTPS enabled
   - CDN caching configured
   - Security headers implemented

2. Backend (api.omniposting.com):
   - Automatic deployment on main branch
   - Rate limiting enabled
   - CORS configured
   - Health monitoring active

## Security Guidelines

1. Credential Management:
   - Never commit sensitive data
   - Use environment variables
   - Follow least privilege principle
   - Rotate credentials regularly

2. Code Security:
   - Input validation
   - SQL injection prevention
   - XSS protection
   - CSRF protection

## Testing Requirements

1. Frontend:
   - Component unit tests
   - Integration tests
   - Visual regression tests
   - Accessibility tests

2. Backend:
   - API endpoint tests
   - Service unit tests
   - Integration tests
   - Performance tests

## Documentation

1. API Documentation:
   - OpenAPI/Swagger specs
   - Authentication flows
   - Rate limits
   - Error responses

2. Frontend Documentation:
   - Component storybook
   - Theme guidelines
   - Layout system
   - Form validation

## Monitoring

1. Frontend:
   - Error tracking
   - Performance monitoring
   - User analytics
   - Loading metrics

2. Backend:
   - API metrics
   - Error logging
   - Performance tracking
   - Database monitoring


## Credential Management

### Required Credentials
1. Infrastructure Access:
   - DigitalOcean Droplet (137.184.15.8)
   - Contact: rowdyroque8@gmail.com for SSH key access
   - Access Level: Root via SSH key authentication

2. Database Access:
   - Neon PostgreSQL Instance
   - Request access through team lead
   - Connection string format: postgresql://user:pass@host/database

3. Environment Variables:
   Frontend (.env):
   ```
   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.omniposting.com
   NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://omniposting.com
   ```

   Backend (.env):
   ```
   PORT=3001
   DATABASE_URL=[request from database admin]
   JWT_SECRET=[request from security team]
   OPENAI_API_KEY=[request from team lead]
   ```

### Credential Access Process
1. Development Environment Setup:
   - Copy .env.example to .env in both frontend and backend
   - Request credentials from team lead (rowdyroque8@gmail.com)
   - Use secure channels for credential transmission
   - Never commit .env files to repository

2. Production Credentials:
   - Managed via DigitalOcean environment configuration
   - Access restricted to DevOps team
   - Rotation schedule: Every 90 days
   - Emergency rotation process documented in internal wiki

3. Access Request Process:
   a. Email request to rowdyroque8@gmail.com
   b. Include:
      - Team role (UI/UX or Backend)
      - Required access level
      - Project justification
   c. Follow security onboarding process
   d. Sign NDA if required

4. Security Guidelines:
   - Never share credentials via unsecured channels
   - Do not store credentials in code or documentation
   - Report any potential security issues immediately
   - Use environment variables for all sensitive data
   - Rotate personal access tokens regularly


## Credential Access Instructions (PRIVATE REPOSITORY)

### Development Environment Setup
1. Request access from team lead (rowdyroque8@gmail.com) with:
   - Your GitHub username
   - Team role (UI/UX or Backend)
   - Required access level

2. You will receive:
   - SSH key for DigitalOcean access (137.184.15.8)
   - Environment variables file (.env)
   - Database connection details
   - API credentials

### Required Environment Variables
Frontend (.env):
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.omniposting.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://omniposting.com
```

Backend (.env):
```
PORT=3001
DATABASE_URL=[Neon PostgreSQL connection string]
JWT_SECRET=[Production JWT secret]
OPENAI_API_KEY=[Production API key]
```

### Security Guidelines
1. Never commit credentials to the repository
2. Store all sensitive data in environment variables
3. Use .env.example for template, not actual values
4. Rotate credentials according to security policy
5. Report any security concerns immediately


## UI/UX Deployment to DigitalOcean

### Deployment Process
1. Create Pull Request:
   ```bash
   # Create feature branch
   git checkout -b devin/ui-feature-name
   
   # Make your changes and commit
   git add packages/frontend/src/components/* packages/frontend/src/app/*
   git commit -m "feat: your feature description"
   
   # Push branch and create PR
   git push origin devin/ui-feature-name
   gh pr create --title "UI: Your feature title" --body "Description of your changes"
   ```

2. After PR Approval and Merge:
   - Changes will be automatically deployed to DigitalOcean
   - Frontend accessible at: https://omniposting.com
   - Backend API at: https://api.omniposting.com

3. Deployment Monitoring:
   - Monitor PM2 logs on DigitalOcean
   - Check deployment status in GitHub Actions
   - Verify changes at https://omniposting.com
   - Test functionality in production
   - Monitor error logs

4. Troubleshooting:
   - Check PM2 logs: Contact DevOps team
   - Deployment issues: Check GitHub Actions
   - Access issues: Contact rowdyroque8@gmail.com

Note: DO NOT deploy to Vercel. All deployments are handled through DigitalOcean via our CI/CD pipeline.


## Important Note on UI/UX Deployments
For security reasons, merging to main branch requires repository admin approval:

1. After creating your PR:
   - Request review from rowdyroque8@gmail.com
   - Wait for approval and merge by repository admin
   - DO NOT attempt to merge directly to main

2. Post-Merge Deployment:
   - After admin merges your PR to main
   - Changes will automatically deploy to DigitalOcean
   - Monitor deployment at https://omniposting.com

Contact rowdyroque8@gmail.com for any deployment or merge issues.

